### Soft Body Physics in Real-Time

Position-Based Dynamics (PBD) is the standard real-time soft body approach:

1. Predict positions: `p_i* = p_i + Δt·v_i`
2. Solve constraints (stretch, bend, volume preservation) iteratively
3. Update velocities: `v_i = (p_i* - p_i) / Δt`

The volume preservation constraint gives "squash and stretch": `Σ (volume_tetrahedra - V_rest) = 0`. This can be solved on GPU as a parallel constraint satisfaction pass. Maps onto agent avatar behavior: a heavily loaded agent "bulges" (volume conservation under stress force), an idle agent "deflates" slightly.

