## 4. Spatial Interaction Paradigms

### Gaze-Based Selection in VR

**Technical Pattern (WebXR):**
```javascript
// Foveated rendering: use gaze direction to concentrate render budget
const eyeGaze = frame.getPose(gazeSpace, referenceSpace);
const gazeDirection = new THREE.Vector3(
  eyeGaze.transform.matrix[8],
  eyeGaze.transform.matrix[9],
  eyeGaze.transform.matrix[10]
).negate();

// Raycaster from gaze
raycaster.set(gazeOrigin, gazeDirection);
const intersects = raycaster.intersectObjects(agentNodes);
```

**Dwell Time Selection:** The dominant pattern is gaze + dwell time (typically 700-1200ms for confirmation). A visual radial progress indicator fills during dwell to provide feedback without requiring a button press. Research confirms gaze targeting matches controller performance for world-locked and body-locked targets.

**Combined Gaze + Pinch:** Apple Vision Pro uses gaze for targeting (which object) and pinch gesture for confirmation (select it). This separates the "point" and "click" into natural physiological channels. The SIAgent framework (2025) uses LLM-powered eye-hand motion intent understanding to predict what the user intends to select before they complete the gesture.

