**Recommended Gesture Vocabulary for Agent Control:**

| Gesture | Agent Action | Detection Method |
|---|---|---|
| Index+thumb pinch | Select agent / confirm action | `distance(thumb-tip, index-finger-tip) < 2cm` |
| Open palm facing out | Pause/freeze agent | Palm normal `dot` viewDir `> 0.8` + fingers extended |
| Grab (all fingers curl) | Drag agent in topology graph | All finger-tip to palm distances `< threshold` |
| Two-handed pull apart | Zoom into agent detail | Bilateral hand separation increasing |
| Flick wrist outward | Dismiss / close panel | Angular velocity `> 5 rad/s` for 200ms |
| Two-handed push away | Send agent to background cluster | Both palms facing scene, moving forward |
| Thumbs up | Approve agent plan | Thumb extended, others curled, orientation up |

**Gorilla Arm Problem:** Extended hand-in-air interaction causes fatigue. Design constraint: agent control panels should sit at elbow height, not shoulder height. Minimize sustained pinch-hold operations. Prefer discrete gestures over continuous manipulation.

**Handy.js** provides pose recognition on top of raw WebXR joint data for browser-based implementations.

