### Progressive Detail Reveal Based on Proximity

**Implementation Pattern:**
```javascript
function updateAgentLOD(agentMesh, camera) {
  const dist = camera.position.distanceTo(agentMesh.position);

  if (dist < 1.0) {
    // Full detail: ray-marched SDF, real-time metrics readout, episode history
    showFullDetail(agentMesh);
  } else if (dist < 3.0) {
    // Medium: polygon mesh, last 5 events, status indicator
    showMediumDetail(agentMesh);
  } else if (dist < 8.0) {
    // Low: billboard sprite, health color only
    showLowDetail(agentMesh);
  } else {
    // Minimal: dot in agent graph topology only
    showMinimalDetail(agentMesh);
  }
}
```

**Progressive Meshes (Hoppe, 1996):** The mathematical foundation is the "edge collapse" operation: `M → M'` by collapsing edge `(u, v)` to a new vertex `w`. The inverse "vertex split" `M' → M` restores detail. A full mesh can be encoded as a sequence of vertex splits that progressively increase detail. WebGL/WebGPU implementations can decode splits dynamically as the user approaches.

**Data Layer Progression for Agent Detail:**
| Distance | Geometry | Data Shown |
|---|---|---|
| 0-0.5m | Full SDF raymarched creature | All telemetry: CPU, memory, active tools, tool call count, last error |
| 0.5-2m | Medium polygon mesh, SSS material | Current task description, state machine node, last 10 events |
| 2-5m | Low polygon, flat shading | Agent name, role badge, health color |
| 5-15m | Billboard quad, pre-baked | Colored dot with status icon |
| 15m+ | Instanced particle | Color coded by cluster |

