### Color Interpolation and Half-Block Pixel Rendering

True color gradient using the `palette` crate + half-block trick for 2x vertical resolution:

```rust
use palette::{Okhsv, Srgb, FromColor};

// Map (x, y) position to RGB via HSV color space
let hue = x as f32 * 360.0 / width as f32;
let value = (height - y) as f32 / height as f32;
let color = Okhsv::new(hue, saturation, value);
let rgb: Srgb<u8> = Srgb::<f32>::from_color_unclamped(color).into_format();
let color = Color::Rgb(rgb.red, rgb.green, rgb.blue);

// Half-block pixel technique: 2 rows per terminal cell
// '▀' = upper half block. fg = top pixel, bg = bottom pixel
buf[Position::new(x, y)]
    .set_char('▀')
    .set_fg(colors[row * 2][col])
    .set_bg(colors[row * 2 + 1][col]);
```

### Unicode Sparklines

Eight Unicode block characters for sparkline rendering (U+2581 through U+2588):
```
▁▂▃▄▅▆▇█  (Lower 1/8 through Full Block)
```

Mapping algorithm:
```rust
fn to_sparkline(data: &[f64]) -> String {
    const BARS: &[char] = &['▁', '▂', '▃', '▄', '▅', '▆', '▇', '█'];
    let min = data.iter().cloned().fold(f64::INFINITY, f64::min);
    let max = data.iter().cloned().fold(f64::NEG_INFINITY, f64::max);
    let extent = if (max - min).abs() < f64::EPSILON { 1.0 } else { max - min };
    data.iter().map(|&v| {
        let normalized = (v - min) / extent;
        let idx = ((normalized * (BARS.len() - 1) as f64).round() as usize)
            .min(BARS.len() - 1);
        BARS[idx]
    }).collect()
}
```

ratatui's built-in `Sparkline` widget now accepts `IntoIterator<Item = SparklineBar>` where `SparklineBar` wraps `Option<u64>` (distinguishing absent from zero).

