    let spans: Vec<Span> = hints.iter().flat_map(|(key, desc)| {
        vec![
            Span::styled(*key, Style::default().bold()),
            Span::raw(format!(" {} ", desc)),
        ]
    }).collect();
    frame.render_widget(Line::from(spans), area);
}
```

### Slash Commands and Autocomplete

Pattern from modern CLI agents (opencode-style):
- `/` at start of input triggers command mode
- `@` triggers fuzzy file/context mention
- `!` triggers shell passthrough mode
- Commands registered with both a slash name and a palette ID
- Emacs/readline bindings for text editing within the prompt: `ctrl+a/e` (line start/end), `ctrl+k` (kill to EOL), `ctrl+u` (kill to BOL), `ctrl+w` (kill word)

