## Backpressure and Flow Control

### Adaptive Coalescing

The coalescing windows adapt to client connection speed to prevent buffer bloat:

```rust
/// Adaptive coalescing parameters.
pub struct CoalesceConfig {
    /// Base coalescing window for agent output
    pub output_window_ms: u64,      // default: 100
    /// Base window for token counts
    pub token_window_ms: u64,       // default: 500
    /// Maximum events in flight before dropping low-priority
    pub max_in_flight: usize,       // default: 1000
    /// Priority levels (higher = more important, never dropped)
    pub priority_threshold: u8,     // default: 5 (gate_result, cfactor_update)
}

/// Event priority for backpressure decisions.
pub fn event_priority(event: &ServerEvent) -> u8 {
    match event {
        ServerEvent::GateResult { .. }      => 10,  // never drop
        ServerEvent::PlanPhaseChange { .. } => 9,
        ServerEvent::AgentExited { .. }     => 8,
        ServerEvent::CFactorUpdate { .. }   => 7,
        ServerEvent::AgentSpawned { .. }    => 6,
        ServerEvent::AgentOutput { .. }     => 3,   // coalesce aggressively
        ServerEvent::WebhookReceived { .. } => 2,
    }
}
```

### Ring Buffer Implementation

```rust
/// Fixed-capacity ring buffer for event replay on reconnection.
pub struct EventRingBuffer {
    events: Vec<(u64, ServerEvent)>,  // (seq, event) pairs
    head: usize,
    capacity: usize,
    next_seq: u64,
}

impl EventRingBuffer {
    pub fn new(capacity: usize) -> Self {
        Self { events: Vec::with_capacity(capacity), head: 0, capacity, next_seq: 0 }
    }

    pub fn push(&mut self, event: ServerEvent) -> u64 {
        let seq = self.next_seq;
        self.next_seq += 1;
        if self.events.len() < self.capacity {
            self.events.push((seq, event));
        } else {
            self.events[self.head] = (seq, event);
        }
        self.head = (self.head + 1) % self.capacity;
        seq
    }

    /// Replay events from `after_seq` for reconnecting clients.
    pub fn replay_from(&self, after_seq: u64) -> Vec<&(u64, ServerEvent)> {
        self.events.iter()
            .filter(|(seq, _)| *seq > after_seq)
            .collect()
    }
}
```

